cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.CR 

The paper proposes a ship tracking method using computer vision and artificial intelligence technologies, which suggests that it belongs to the computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The method also involves bounding box regression and key points matching for scale prediction, which are common techniques in robotics (cs.RO) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper addresses the problem of maritime security, which could fall under the sub-category of cryptography and security (cs.CR).
